verbose_text: Because the TiO 2 -SiO 2 and B 2 O 3 -SiO 2 joins have a large two-phase liquid region XREF_BIBR, it is reasonable to assume that the ternary SrO-B 2 O 3 -SiO 2 and SrO-TiO 2 -SiO 2 systems exhibit immiscibility or phase separation; and ii) for SiO 2 < 30 mol%, the immiscible region decreased towards the SrO-TiO 2 join, probably due to the decrease in the glass former.
evidence: SiO 2  <30 mol%, the immiscible region decreased towards the SrO-TiO 2  join
